		{"id":"da4ef755c9a9691c","type":"text","text":"- Growth\n\t- Compounding\n\t- Exponential\n- Durability, Survival comes before growth\n","x":980,"y":1032,"width":250,"height":177},
		{"id":"6bddb7fe28263e15","type":"text","text":"- Durability\n\t- Fragility\n\t- Vulnerability\n- Time\n\t- will it survie Decades and centuries","x":980,"y":1273,"width":250,"height":227},
		{"id":"b4c2fb97f2b90bcb","type":"text","text":"[[Progress]]","x":320,"y":-800,"width":250,"height":50},
		{"id":"b72db534fbb367e4","type":"text","text":"[[Tradsmenship]]","x":330,"y":-1040,"width":231,"height":140},
		{"id":"3df4e2ce57f68a2b","type":"text","text":"# 7 Monopoly  Questions Protocol\n1. The Engineering Question\n\tCan you create breakthrough technology instead of incremental improvements?\t\t[[THE ENGINEERING QUESTION 10x]]\n2. The Timing Question\n\tIs now the right time to start your particular business? [[THE TIMING QUESTION]]\n3. The Monopoly Question\n\tAre you starting with a big share of a small market? [[THE MONOPOLY QUESTION-highly attainable over highly competitive]]\n4. The People Question\n\tDo you have the right team? [[THE PEOPLE QUESTION]]\n5. The Distribution Question\n\tDo you have a way to not just create but deliver your product? [[Craft/Tradecraft/Business/Monopoly/7 Questions/THE DISTRIBUTION QUESTION - the world is a labotory]]\n6. The Durability Question\n\tWill your market position be defensible 10 and 20 years into the future? [[THE DURABILITY QUESTIO -The last mover]]\n7. The Secret Question\n\tHave you identified a unique opportunity that others don’t see?[[Tradesecret Unconventional Truth Secret Question]]","x":1860,"y":425,"width":940,"height":475},
		{"id":"3929f25277def54b","type":"text","text":"speed","x":1362,"y":455,"width":250,"height":60},
		{"id":"d3f07c6a5fdc3404","type":"text","text":"Money In","x":1362,"y":515,"width":250,"height":50},
		{"id":"2aa45b57903635f5","type":"text","text":"- Dominate the smallest niche, the right cluster\n- Scale up\n\t- Scale to related Broder Markets\n\t- Expand no of users or markets\n- Founding narrative\n\t- Dominate niche and then scale to adjacent markets\n- Disruption\n\t- Never disrupt, disruption is picking fight you cannot fight \n\t- its loking for trouble and finding it","x":1371,"y":590,"width":250,"height":530},
		{"id":"d21399b34fc3bd1c","type":"text","text":"- Escape competition will give you a monopoly\n- Monopoly profits is in the future\n- Value of business is all the money it will make in the future, discounted future cash flow with the present\n    Simply stated, the value of a business today is the sum of all the money it will make in the future. (**To properly value a business, you also have to discount those future cash flows to their present worth, since a given amount of money today is worth more than the same amount in the future.**)\n- Low-Growth Business vs high Growth startups\n\tComparing discounted cash flows shows the difference between low-growth businesses and high-growth startups at its starkest.\n\t\n\tMost of the value of low-growth businesses is in the near term.\n- Loose money initially\n\t- then get permament monopoly profits","x":1866,"y":1076,"width":619,"height":455},
